<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-993] Image transparency lost when drawing an image (during pdf to image conversion)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-993</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;My scenario is converting an existing PDF to an image.  When the PDF contains an image with transparency the transparency is lost and the image is drawn at 100% opacity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This fix is related (and depends on) the issue:  &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-975&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-975&lt;/a&gt;  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;All that is needed is to set the composite of the graphics before drawing the image as specified in the graphics state (See attached patch)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note:  line number in patch maybe off since it was created from 1.5.0 but after fixing 975.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
