                            <comment id="13012991" author="jeichar" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2011 14:38:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fix for this issue.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13013520" author="lehmi" created="Wed, 30 Mar 2011 15:52:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good to me. Can you provide us with a sample pdf to demonstrates the improvement?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13013850" author="jeichar" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2011 06:22:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;PNG with two overlapping images.  The top one has 50% transparency&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13013853" author="jeichar" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2011 06:28:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;pdf with two overlapping images.  The top image has 50% transparency.&lt;br/&gt;
also attached 2 images.  The first is generated by pdfbox pdf to image before fix and after fix.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13013854" author="jeichar" created="Thu, 31 Mar 2011 06:30:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This contains the same code as other patch but adds in a few lines for setting the composite when drawing text.  The reason is that if an image is drawn and the composite is set when drawing the image.   Then text will be drawn with the same composite setting which is a bug.  So I reset the composite in the draw text method.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13015159" author="lehmi" created="Sun, 3 Apr 2011 15:22:20 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I added the patch in revision 1088324 as proposed and added also one missing setColor() within the text drawing section&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the contribution&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
